                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00Sonora/127: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Vera Cruz</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Myers</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vera Cruz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-03-07T17:00:00-06:00"
                            >March 7, 1929—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:18 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Vera Cruz again under Federal control. Custom house and other government offices
                    opened this afternoon by former Federal employees. Federal troops on the way to
                    Vera Cruz from Jalapa and Cordoba. Colonel Cervantez has the situation in hand
                    and there is no disorder. Municipal authorities resumed duties. Embassy
                    informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Myers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
